<subsection xml:id="linearity-examples">
<title> Examples </title>
	
  <p>
    Let's now look at an example of a linear differential equation.
  </p>

  <example xml:id="example-linearity-01">

    <p>
      Determine if the following differential equation is linear.
      <me> y'' + \frac{y'}{x^2} + y = 17x </me>.
    </p>

    <solution>
      <p>
        This equation is almost in the form (with <m>n=2</m>)
        <xref ref="def-linear"/>.  We just need to make a minor adjustment to
        see all the parts explicity,
        <me>(1)y'' + \left(\frac{1}{x^2}\right)y' + (1)y = 17x</me>
        where (matching with <xref ref="def-linear"/>)
        <me>\DS a_2 = 1, \,\,
          a_1 = \frac{1}{x^2}, \,\,
          a_0 = 1, \,\,\text{ and } \,\,
          f(x) = 17x</me>
      </p>
    </solution>

  </example>

  <exercise><title> Now you Try </title>
    <statement>
      The differential equation,	<m>\DS (1 - x)y'' - 4xy' + 5y = \cos x </m>, is
    </statement>
    
    <choices>

      <choice correct="yes"><statement>Linear</statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Yes! This DE is linear.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>

      <choice><statement>Non-Linear</statement>
        <feedback>No, Try again.</feedback>
      </choice>

    </choices>

  </exercise>
	
</subsection>